<paragraph id="800B928E0F6166FD01AE64CC36A73E29" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName id="35058CE943E85D294E4B079D714D29D0" authorityName="L. Fan &amp; Y. Y. Xu" authorityYear="2018" class="Pezizomycetes" family="Helvellaceae" genus="Barssia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Barssia luyashanensis" order="Pezizales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="luyashanensis">
<emphasis id="A45E63DF9D377A8BB26565F403CB90E1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Barssia luyashanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. Fan &amp; Y.Y. Xu, Phytotaxa 374(2): 134 (2018).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F753FBA6A2707F0F51FB3EB091FFEF0D" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="holotype">
<paragraph id="0694E17EBEB4F7D669A9931C4FC1956A" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Holotype.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1F0DCED350A5269F1BCA3912CB6EB14" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
China. Shanxi Province, Ningwu County, Qiuqiangou Village, Luyashan Mountain, alt. 2100m, 25 August 2017, in soil under 
<taxonomicName id="31071D50C169C53B71F4EA6CD294AD47" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Picea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Picea" order="Pinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4BA2ABE7E597EC6ADE839A6F2B51F6D7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Picea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., M. Chen CM023 (BJTC FAN764).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C751455E479493B4E47EC927252632A7" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis id="71CEFA7EC9FBB7B7C34E2A09CF83BE4F" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Illustrations</emphasis>
- 
<bibRefCitation id="2F5DEE8FA6424915354B57C0CC17CF6E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.374.2.4" author="Xu, YY" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="129 - 138" refId="B42" refString="Xu, YY, Guo, LJ, Li, T, Fan, L, 2018. Two new species of Barssia from China. Phytotaxa 374 (2): 129 - 138, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.374.2.4" title="Two new species of Barssia from China." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.374.2.4" volume="374" year="2018">Xu et al. (2018</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 3)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CC132466E71C317465456123B671B1A1" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="notes">
<paragraph id="96BC6B80242C38724917599D7877870D" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C01BA1D79BEDCA0A8F6C77CDF69AC9E2" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName id="B2012CEAF6C89A8A668569E856757043" class="Pezizomycetes" family="Helvellaceae" genus="Balsamia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Balsamia luyashanensis" order="Pezizales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="luyashanensis">
<emphasis id="C2019722399074178AAABF18C82B0D3D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Balsamia luyashanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also recently described from the Luyashan Mountain of Shanxi Province, China, under 
<taxonomicName id="AB6183D14A9D9F40EDE74287CCC5775A" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Picea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Picea" order="Pinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="47DC8E1A36260A96C80218CD6F6F5767" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Picea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. So far it is known only from the type locality. The species can be recognized by its red brown ascomata with fine warts, gleba without chambers and irregularly clavate asci (
<bibRefCitation id="32754307AE2F1678CBEC2D000CE17F85" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.374.2.4" author="Xu, YY" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="129 - 138" refId="B42" refString="Xu, YY, Guo, LJ, Li, T, Fan, L, 2018. Two new species of Barssia from China. Phytotaxa 374 (2): 129 - 138, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.374.2.4" title="Two new species of Barssia from China." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.374.2.4" volume="374" year="2018">Xu et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). The species was similar in appearance of ascomata to 
<taxonomicName id="48CFB1D549EDD463D5BFA7B351BA037F" genus="B." lsidName="B. gunerii" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="gunerii">
<emphasis id="4E3170D3536202064301D8D446DC52F5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">B. gunerii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6C18E6590EBE2F6BD38511B3FA74815B" genus="B." lsidName="B. hellenica" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="hellenica">
<emphasis id="B4C94C06B4C6052281661F22A2F9A418" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">B. hellenica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but 
<taxonomicName id="B0160B3A82345B994354F351F1EDD2E7" genus="B." lsidName="B. gunerii" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="gunerii">
<emphasis id="9C858F55CB1F0ED1373A125D31AB1529" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">B. gunerii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated by its subglobose to ovoid ascospores and gleba with irregularly sinuous, labyrinth-like veins (
<bibRefCitation id="AAFE31E412AE1E05EA087B8C30FB66AC" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3906/bot-1801-33" author="Dogan, HH" journalOrPublisher="Turkish Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="1 - 8" refId="B10" refString="Dogan, HH, Bozok, F, Taskin, H, 2018. A new species of Barssia (Ascomycota, Helvellaceae) from Turkey. Turkish Journal of Botany 42: 1 - 8, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3906/bot-1801-33" title="A new species of Barssia (Ascomycota, Helvellaceae) from Turkey." url="https://doi.org/10.3906/bot-1801-33" volume="42" year="2018">
<normalizedToken id="6F85EC0EDB74DCCBED6762E1639F2E19" originalValue="DoÄŸan">Dogan</normalizedToken>
et al. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="C584299EF5FC481C385F59D0FEFD5DAF" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2019.42.07" author="Hansen, K" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="186 - 204" refId="B14" refString="Hansen, K, Schumacher, T, Skrede, I, Huhtinen, S, Wang, XH, 2019. Pindara revisited-evolution and generic limits in Helvellaceae. Persoonia 42: 186 - 204, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2019.42.07" title="Pindara revisited-evolution and generic limits in Helvellaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2019.42.07" volume="42" year="2019">Hansen et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
), while 
<taxonomicName id="A6ABE3B1399F5B34465BE354EE8BDD2A" genus="B." lsidName="B. hellenica" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="hellenica">
<emphasis id="776CCE488CD9C26F9E85BC23FC3EEB70" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">B. hellenica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its ovoid ascospores (
<bibRefCitation id="F225117ED069D785E8B7E4E5BC2678D0" author="Kaounas, V" journalOrPublisher="org" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="213 - 219" refId="B18" refString="Kaounas, V, Agnello, C, Alvarado, P, Slavova, M, 2015. Barssia hellenica sp. nov. (Ascomycota, Pezizales), a new hypogeous species from Greece. Ascomycete. org 7 (5): 213 - 219" title="Barssia hellenica sp. nov. (Ascomycota, Pezizales), a new hypogeous species from Greece. Ascomycete." volume="7" year="2015">Kaounas et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="F920AFB7987E17B8FDFC247A35FCA998" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2019.42.07" author="Hansen, K" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="186 - 204" refId="B14" refString="Hansen, K, Schumacher, T, Skrede, I, Huhtinen, S, Wang, XH, 2019. Pindara revisited-evolution and generic limits in Helvellaceae. Persoonia 42: 186 - 204, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2019.42.07" title="Pindara revisited-evolution and generic limits in Helvellaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2019.42.07" volume="42" year="2019">Hansen et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
